remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="9044d-118">参数的默认值 `value` 使用空字符串 ( "" ) 。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-118">The default for the `value` parameter uses the empty string ("").</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9044d-119">`value` <xref:System.Net.Cookie> Visual Basic) 中的参数不能是 `null` 引用 (。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-119">The `value` parameter for a <xref:System.Net.Cookie> must not be a `null` reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9044d-120">分号 ( ";") 和逗号 ( "、" ) 字符被保留，并且不能在参数中传递， `value` 除非传入参数的字符串 `value` 用双引号引起来。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-120">The semicolon (";") and comma (",") characters are reserved and cannot be passed in the `value` parameter unless the string passed in the `value` parameter is enclosed in double quotes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9044d-121">因此，下面的示例构造函数将会成功，但当你尝试 <xref:System.Net.Cookie> 使用或方法将其添加到 <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> 实例时 <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> ，该操作将失败并引发异常：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-121">So the following example constructor would succeed, but when you try to add this <xref:System.Net.Cookie> to a <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instance with the <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> or <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> methods, the operation will fail and throw an exception:</span></span>  
  
 ```csharp
 System.Net.Cookie cookie = new System.Net.Cookie("contoso", "123,456");
 cookie.Domain = "contoso.com";
 new CookieContainer().Add(cookie);
 ```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9044d-122">但是，以下具有转义的特殊字符的构造函数将创建 <xref:System.Net.Cookie> 可添加到 <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> 实例的：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-122">However, the following constructor with these special characters escaped will create a <xref:System.Net.Cookie> that can be added to a <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instance:</span></span>  
 
 ```csharp
 System.Net.Cookie cookie = new System.Net.Cookie("contoso", "\"123,456\"");
 cookie.Domain = "contoso.com";
 new CookieContainer().Add(cookie);
 ```
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9044d-123">逗号字符用作同一行中单独 cookie 之间的分隔符。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-123">The comma character is used as a delimiter between separate cookies on the same line.</span></span>

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="9044d-141">参数的默认值 `path` 使用空字符串 ( "" ) 。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-141">The default for the `path` parameter uses the empty string ("").</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9044d-142">`value` <xref:System.Net.Cookie> Visual Basic) 中的参数不能是 `null` 引用 (。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-142">The `value` parameter for a <xref:System.Net.Cookie> must not be a `null` reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9044d-143">分号 ( ";") 和逗号 ( "、" ) 字符被保留，并且不能在参数中传递， `value` 除非传入参数的字符串 `value` 用双引号引起来。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-143">The semicolon (";") and comma (",") characters are reserved and cannot be passed in the `value` parameter unless the string passed in the `value` parameter is enclosed in double quotes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9044d-144">因此，下面的示例构造函数将会成功，但当你尝试 <xref:System.Net.Cookie> 使用或方法将其添加到 <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> 实例时 <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> ，该操作将失败并引发异常：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9044d-144">So the following example constructor would succeed, but when you try to add this <xref:System.Net.Cookie> to a <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer> instance with the <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Net.Cookie)> or <xref:System.Net.CookieContainer.Add(System.Uri,System.Net.Cookie)> methods, the operation will fail and throw an exception:</span></span>  
  
